// Example build-time configuration for RizeMobile.
//
// This file is committed and provides safe defaults for every
// configurable build setting, so `make generate`/`make build`/`make test`
// work out of the box on a fresh clone with no setup.
//
// To override any value locally (e.g. to point at a staging backend)
// without touching this file or project.yml, and without committing your
// change:
//   1. Copy this file to `Config.local.xcconfig` (already gitignored).
//   2. Set the values you want to override there.
//   3. Run `make generate` to regenerate the Xcode project.
// The #include? below pulls in Config.local.xcconfig if it exists, and its
// settings win because the include is last in this file.

// RIZ-46: the sync/auth API's base URL. Flows through project.yml's
// `configFiles` into this xcconfig, then into Info.plist's
// RIZE_BACKEND_BASE_URL key, and is read at runtime by
// `BackendConfigProvider.resolve()`. A `UserDefaults` override
// (`BackendConfigProvider.backendBaseURLDefaultsKey`) still takes priority
// over this value at runtime, for on-device QA without a rebuild.
RIZE_BACKEND_BASE_URL = http://localhost:8080

// Local overrides — must stay last so Config.local.xcconfig wins.
#include? "Config.local.xcconfig"
